cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.SC. 

The paper deals with a geometric problem of finding the onion decomposition of a set of points in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The solution involves building a data structure (cs.DS) that can handle a set of pairwise disjoint unit disks, and using it to preprocess the input points. The algorithmic techniques used include recursive space decomposition (cs.DM), convex layers (cs.GR), and fast union of onion decompositions (cs.SC).
